4:
...This world is governed by light, but
ruled by cruelty.
8:
By my hand, however, there will be
healing.
14:
I am the Magnificent Witch Cipher,
chilly preserver of both time and
fate! Behold my new attire!
22:
I'm glad you think so. The Academy
had it custom-made for me!
27:
We've got high hopes for you. We'll
be relying on your talents more
often now that you're a fully-fledged
teacher.
31:
Huh? I thought you were just taking
a few classes?
36:
Haha... I'm the Magnificent Witch,
after all. The teacher helping me
with breaking Rei's curse asked me if
I'd like to teach.
45:
She does not lie. Indeed, you could
say she was quite sought after.
53:
Even more so than my Oculus, her
power is truly something else. It
caught the attention of some of the
higher-ups at the Academy.
58:
Reylas has joined us as well, after
being scouted by some of the other
teachers. He's on the same team as
Cipher.
61:
Unlike Couette's powers, Cipher's
can be considered part of the Water
element category... though only
barely so.
65:
There is quite a difference... I still
struggle to understand her abilities
myself.
71:
Whatever do you mean? We're
much the same, aren't we, Reylas?
Masters of ice, refusing to thaw!
75:
...I suppose we are. I want to save
my brother, and your sister. Let
us do our best together.
80:
You sure nobody'll catch a cold with
this difference in temperature?
85:
You mustn't let your natural talent
excuse you from your studies,
Cipher. You still haven't read this,
have you?
93:
Professor Leleni recently selected
this book to be included in the
elementary course curriculum. It's
quite the read, I assure you.
98:
I... Um...
Yes, I know, but...
102:
But still! These books at the
Academy are always weirdly
esoteric or needlessly dry!
105:
Sometimes I wonder if we really
need to pile on all this theoretical
stuff!
109:
But... I'll keep at it. Rei's waiting for
me, after all.
114: Yes. We've all got high hopes for you.
121:
A cry for help! Looks like it's time to
teach someone a lesson!
126:
ANOTHER golem?! Why do they keep
showing up?!
130:
Don't you dare lay a finger on my
students.
138: Freeze, shatter, and be no more.
141:
You showed 'em, Professor Cipher!
You're so powerful even without
incantations!
146:
Are you all unharmed? It didn't hurt
any of you, did it?
149: We're good thanks to you, Teach!
152:
I'm glad I made it in time. I couldn't
bear to see any of you injured.
155:
Now, if you'll excuse me. The ice
won't melt unless I take my leave.
163:
Yeah... Pretty incredible. And the
students' reaction... They love you.
168:
Even without an incantation, you
show impressive talent.
173:
We can only hope that ice actually
melts.
180:
...And that's how things went. I wish
you could have seen my excellent
performance, Stella.
194:
You're totes exaggerating. Stella,
don't take anything Ciph says too
seriously, got it?
196:
Schoolgirls staring at her with hearts
for eyes? Please.
202:
Really?! No way...
This Voluntas place must be working
wonders for Ciph.
205:
Heh. I won't stop growing either,
dear sister. I hope you didn't think I
was stagnating?
208:
I've made friends with some of the
faculty, as well. Professor Leleni is
adorable and kind, and Professor
Nicola is considerate and easygoing.
211: Sounds like they treat you nice, huh...
213:
Bring your fans next time, they
sound cool. I bet they'd be up for
TP'ing a faculty building or two.
219:
...What do you say, Rei? Would you
like to visit the Academy?
222: You nut. You forget about the ice?
228:
That's why you've gotta do
something about this cage I'm in,
'kay?
230:
You're gonna keep growing, yeah?
You're close to fixing this, I can feel it.
232:
I'm counting on you to get me outta
here, "dear sister."
239:
I AM the Magnificent Witch Cipher,
after all!
